# Styling conventions

This project uses **Vanilla Extract**, not Tailwind. Do not assume `tailwind.config` or utility-first Tailwind classes unless a file already uses them.

## Vanilla Extract

- Component and theme styles live in **`*.css.ts`** files (e.g. `theme.css.ts`, `atoms.css.ts`, component `Foo.css.ts`).
- Use **recipes** and **atoms** patterns already defined under `src/style/` for repeatable styling.
- Import sprinkles/atoms from the established paths (e.g. `style/atoms.css`, `style/theme.css.ts`) — follow imports in existing components.

## Design tokens

- Shared tokens live under **`src/style/tokens/`**: breakpoints, colors, spacing, typography, shadows, borders, z-indices.
- Prefer **semantic token usage** (via atoms/theme) over hard-coded pixel or hex values in new UI.

## Class composition

- Use **`clsx`** for conditional class names and merging with `className` props.
- When extending layout primitives, pass through `className` and merge with `clsx` like existing `Box` usage.

## Global CSS

- App-wide entry styles are wired through imports such as `@/style/app.css` in the root layout — keep global rules minimal; prefer component-level Vanilla Extract.
